Package uk.ac.manchester.spinnaker.data_spec

Class MemoryRegionCollection

java.lang.Object
uk.ac.manchester.spinnaker.data_spec.MemoryRegionCollection
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Iterable<MemoryRegion>, java.util.Collection<MemoryRegion>
public final class MemoryRegionCollection
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Collection<MemoryRegion>
A collection of memory regions. Note that the collection cannot be modified by the standard collection API; those modification operations will fail. The set(...) operation works.
Author:
Donal Fellows

    • needsToWriteRegion

      public boolean needsToWriteRegion​(int regionID)
      Get whether a particular region needs to be written.
      Parameters:
      regionID - The ID of the region to check.
      Returns:
      True if the region must be written. A region must be written if it is filled or if it has a region after it that must be written.
      Throws:
      java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If a bad region ID is given
